<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-923-488  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 923 488  OV: 07 923 402.andM; </DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Nov 27 1989 v6 n47 p80(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Successfully breaks rules: Forth Inc., PolyForth ISD-4, $2,950(PC, AT) or $3,850 (386). (Software Review ) (one of sixevaluations in 'High-level operating systems make PCs run likeminis') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Coffee, Peter; Dang, Lori J.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Forth language development tools and the Forth-based pF/xoperating system are combined in Forth Inc's PolyForth ISD-4,priced at $2950 for a PC or AT model microcomputer or $3,850 foran Intel 80386-based system.andP;  It is an unusual operating systemwhich provides transparent virtual-memory management and theability to load blocks of application code on demand from disk.andO;Code that can be stored in ROM can be distinguished from thatwhich cannot by the programmer, useful for developing applicationsto be embedded in hardware.andP;  Users are pleased PolyForth.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   FORTH Inc. (products).andO;Product:   PolyForth ISD-4 (Operating system).andO;Topic:     MultitaskingEvaluationOperating Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Successfully Breaks RulesandM;FORTH INC., POLYFORTH ISD-4, $2,950andM;(PC, AT) OR $3,850 (386)andM;PolyForth combines Forth language-development tools with the Forth-based pF/xmultitasking operating system.andP;  It breaks all the usual rules about divisionof labor between an operating system and an applications-developmentenvironment.andP;  For example, there are no disk files; disk space is addresseddirectly by applications in 1K-byte blocks.andM;This pays off with transparent virtual-memory management -- applications canbe written as though every disk block is always in memory, with pF/x loadingblocks on demand, if needed.andM;A Database Support package lets developers build their applications in a moretraditional manner.andP;  For instance, it permits the use of language constructsthat behave like named files.andM;Forth allows the programmer to distinguish between portions of code that canand cannot be stored in ROM, a convenience for applications that can beembedded in hardware.andP;  Other Forth constructs simplify the interface withcontrol panels and other devices.andM;Forth Inc. can be reached in Manhattan Beach, Calif., at (213) 372-8493.andM;----------Buyers say: Low memory overheadandM;&quot;It gives the best performance per dollar over [most] any other system andgives [us] expandability, which means that we can build one application ontop of another application and add new operating systems functions easily,&quot;claimed Dave Robinson, manager of controls engineering at Brown Machine Inc.,andO;a manufacturer of machine tools in Beaverton, Mich.andM;&quot;A lot of users may find something like QNX easier to use than PolyForth, butPolyForth requires less overhead and less memory.andP;  PolyForth's nucleus isabout 8K [bytes.] &quot;andM;According to Robinson, the firm exchanges some functionality to gain speedand performance.andM;Greg Lisle, senior development engineer at Fairchild Industrial Products Co.,andO;a producer of industrial-control equipment in Winston-Salem, N.C., claimsPolyForth is quite reliable.andP;  And, when the system does crash, it is easy torecover the data.andM;According to Lisle, PolyForth's &quot;transparency and extensibility&quot; makes iteasy for users to develop and enhance applications.andM;&quot;You can program Forth by extending the language and adding newinstructions,&quot; he said.andP;  &quot;With most programming languages, it is difficult tomanipulate the hardware functions directly.andP;  With Forth, it is quite easy dueto the language itself.&quot;andM;</TEXT></DOC>